      • partition

        private static int partition(java.lang.String[] arr,
            int p,
            int r)
        Partitions a conceptual array by choosing a pivot randomly and goes through each element moving them either to the left or to the right of the pivot.
        Parameters:
        p - left bound on conceptual piece of array
        r - right bound on conceptual piece of array
        Returns:
        int pivot index, basically says everything to the left of me stays on the left, everything to the right stays right, and I'm in the perfect spot.
